.mod-intro
  %h2 Turing Turns Great Aptitude Into Great Developers.
  %p 
    Being a developer takes the right mix of passion, curiosity, creativity, and confidence. We’ve found that combination across a variety of backgrounds including financial analysts, warehouse managers, bartenders, musicians and electrical enginees. If you show the right aptitude and are ready to work hard, we’ll turn you into a professional software developer.
  %p= link_to 'Apply now', 'http://apply.turing.io', class: "button"

.mod-columns
  .layout-wrap
    %h2 The Difference

    .col.first
      %h3 Instruction
      %p 
        Being a good developer does not prepare you to teach development. The Turing staff blends programming experience with years of classroom instruction. No other team can match our depth of expertise and on-the-ground instructional experience.

    .col
      %h3 Curriculum
      %p 
        No other program approaches the depth of expertise our students develop. Beyond simple Rails applications, our students master Test-Driven Development, build and consume APIs, implement systems of coordinating applications, and understand strong Object-Oriented design.
    .col
      %h3 Results
      %p 
        We build professional developers. Our seven-month instructional program is carefully crafted to prepare high-aptitude individuals for careers as software developers. Succeed in our program and you won’t just be an intern, you’ll be valuable.

    %p= link_to 'Learn more', '/difference.html', class: 'button gray'

.mod-quote{style: "background-image: url(#{image_path('bg_quote1.jpg')})"}
  .layout-wrap
    %blockquote
      “I chose this program because was the only one that promised to produce professional developers and not just a kickstart. I had no computer science background and needed to have a real job at the end of it. <br/><br/>We learned by doing – by working together to build real web apps, completely immersed in programming. Now I use those skills every day at <a href="http://turbovote.org" target="_blank">TurboVote</a>.“
      %footer – Jennifer Eliuk

